article.headline: Georgia State 61, Delaware 44
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Lance Perique scored a game-high 19 points and Leonard Mendez and Rashad Chase each added 12 points, and Georgia State defeated Delaware 61-44 Wednesday night. Georgia State (7-10, 3-4) expanded a six-point halftime lead to double figures at 48-37 at 8:06 and kept it in double figures for the rest of the game. In the first half, Georgia State jumped out to a quick 6-0 lead before the Blue Hens made a free throw at 16:32 to get on the board. The Panthers hit 8 of their first 11 shots in opening a 16-7 lead at 12:26, with Perique scoring eight of those 16 points. Chase also grabbed a game-high 15 rebounds for Georgia State (7-10, 3-4 CAA). Calvin Cannon led the Blue Hens (3-15, 1-6 CAA) with 11 points while Herb Courtney contributed 10 points and a career-high 14 rebounds.
